@question
If the worshipper does not recite any verse of the Quran after the Fatiha in the two rakahs (units) of the prayer, is his prayer valid?
@answer
No, the prayer is not valid. This is based on the Quranic verse, "And recite what is revealed to you of the Book and establish prayer. Indeed, prayer prohibits immorality and wrongdoing, and the remembrance of Allah is greater" [Quran 29:45]. Also, in the Hadith of Al-Bukhari, the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) said, "The prayer is not valid without reciting the Quran." [Al-Bukhari]
@source
Al-Bukhari, Sahih Al-Bukhari, Hadith 1, Book 1, Hadith 3.

